commit.message:
Return doctest status via exit code

Exit with unsuccessful code if doctests fail.  This makes it possible
to actually automate running tests without relying on ugly greps
to figure out if they worked.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/nolanl/dnslib into nolanl-master
Check for truncated request in server.py (Issue #9)
Check for truncated request in server.py (Issue #9)

intercept.py: Add --all-qtypes option

Makes intercept return an empty reply for queries where the qname
matched an intercept, but not the qtype.  This is useful for tests
where getting an unexpected AAAA record from the real upstream would
be confusing.

intecept.py: Return SERVFAIL if upstream doesn't respond

This allows tests to differentiate between legit NXDOMAINs and
upstream being slow or broken.

Signed-off-by: Nolan Leake <nolan@sigbus.net>

intercept.py: Add support for per-name upstream forwarding.

Adds a -f/--forward option to allow different upstreams for
different names.  Preserves fallback to the existing upstream.
